Subject: Derived Evidence Review Worker Signal Source

Description: Preserved derived source for the evidence_review_013 worker signal observed during LM Studio corpus benchmarking.

& [DerivedEvidenceReviewWorkerSignalSource] is preserved derived source
  + [source_type] is derived_from_benchmark_observation
  + [observed_subject] is corpus_evidence_review_013
  + [accepted_attempt] is initial attempt passed score 100 strong with exact raw SOP, all evidence review fields, required terms, outside preservation, and no proof or integration overclaim
  + [readiness_effect] is fourth distinct task-family signal meets the minimum pass gate for limited-diverse readiness language
  + [caution_effect] is limited-diverse readiness remains scratch-isolated, prompt-only, non-mutating, validator-gated, and not project-root or broad competence authority
  + [reason_for_change] is evidence review shows the worker can critique weak claims and preserve not integrated status under strict prompt boundaries
  + [outside] is hidden model state, broad LM Studio competence, project-root authority, worker mutation authority, credentials, destructive action, and untested periphery_correlation or integration_disposition families

  = must: preserve the raw worker output as benchmark data
  = must: treat the accepted output as proposal evidence only
  = must: distinguish minimum pass gate from broad readiness
  = must: keep Codex as validator and integration authority
  - never: let a fourth family pass erase outside or grant repo mutation authority
